<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-07-26T12:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-07-26T12:45:00-05:00" n="806" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d806">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.154/50: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-26T12:00:00-05:45">July 26,
                                1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:05 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>204. Department’s 107, July 24, 5 p.m. President Moncada says he will be
                            grateful for either Army or Navy engineers. Of the men available he
                            would of course like those best qualified for the special work he has in
                            mind.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>